title: For Sale:  Taurus PT1911  45cal.
postcontent:
Review:This  PT1911 comes standard with these features: ambidextrous extended safeties, Taurus safety lock in the rowel (Commander-style) hammer, three-dot fixed combat sights, ventilated long trigger, flat backstrap, 8-round magazine (one came with my test pistol) with bumper pad, finely checkered frontstrap and backstrap, checkered synthetic “Double Diamond” style Taurus grips, extended beavertail grip safety, and front cocking serrations. Clearly this is not a bargain basement gun.
The Taurus PT1911 comes with a matte blue finish, giving it a businesslike appearance. Note that the finish is blue and not a modern rust-resistant finish such as Nitex, which means that more attention will need to be given to exterior maintenance
The only thing I did to the PT1911 prior to the range test was to wipe off the extra surface lubrication. I started shooting using the 230-grain FMJ load. From beginning to end, the Taurus PT1911 ran flawlessly. No “break-in” shooting needed here or other excuses for poor initial performance—just the kind of performance one hopes for out of any combat pistol.
The trigger was crisp and broke at around 5 pounds. The sights were aligned to the point of aim and easy to pick up. I enjoyed the mystic feel of this quality 1911 in the hand, which was clearly improved by the fine checkering on the front and backstrap. At 30 feet, the first eight-round group fired two-handed standing landed in a nice 3.5-inch cluster. After a bit more trigger time and a switch to the V-Crown load, I was rewarded with a 2-inch seven-shot group at the same 30 foot distance.
Backing off to 100 yards, I switched back to the SIG FMJ loads. Firing a total of five rounds from the two-handed standing position, I managed a remarkable group. Three of the five rounds fired ended up in another 3.5-inch group in the center of the silhouette! A fourth shot, undoubtedly the product of a lapse in concentration, ended up low and to the right in the leg of the silhouette. The fifth round fired, the product of an even bigger lapse in concentration, ended up somewhere entirely off the paper. Folks, if this pistol can produce this level of accuracy at 100 yards, it is capable of doing anything you could possibly require of it at any standard pistol distance in terms of precision.- Scott WagnerCOMEs: WITH: Case,1 Mag , Cleaning Brush . New Condition test fired only
